data.title: CRAY RESEARCH INC.
data.meta_description: CRAY RESEARCH INC., Eagan, Mich., said Learjet Inc. has acquired a Cray J916 supercomputer. The system, installed at Learjet's R&D facility in Wichita, is being used for computational fluid dynamics (CFD) and finite element analysis (FEA) to support work on new and existing aircraft. It will also be used in simulations to improve quality and efficiency at Learjet, a division of Bombardier Inc. Terms of the order weren't disclosed.
